          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function's business logic involves determining the fiscal year based on the input date. Typically, a fiscal year might not align with the calendar year, starting and ending on different months. The function likely checks the month of the input date and applies a rule to decide whether the fiscal year is the current year or the next year. For example, if the fiscal year starts in October, any date from October to December would belong to the next calendar year."
        }
      ]
    },
